The paper proposes a learning-based approach for navigation using deep convolutional networks, which is a common theme in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) research. The paper also discusses the use of reward structures and deep reinforcement learning, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness and generalization capabilities of the proposed approach, which are important considerations in systems and control (cs.SY).
